ggRandomForests 2.2.0

Print a gg_minimal_depth object.

Source: R/print.gg_minimal_depth.R
print.gg_minimal_depth.Rd

Print a gg_minimal_depth object.

# S3 method for gg_minimal_depth
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

a gg_minimal_depth object.

...

optional arguments

Examples

## ------------------------------------------------------------
## classification example
## ------------------------------------------------------------
## You can build a randomForest
# rfsrc_iris <- rfsrc(Species ~ ., data = iris)
# varsel_iris <- var.select(rfsrc_iris)
# ... or load a cached randomForestSRC object
data(varsel_iris, package="ggRandomForests")

# Get a data.frame containing minimaldepth measures
gg_dta <- gg_minimal_depth(varsel_iris)
print(gg_dta)
#> -----------------------------------------------------------
#> gg_minimal_depth
#> model size         : 2 
#> depth threshold    : 2.1272 
#> 
#> PE :       all     setosa versicolor  virginica 
#>       0.04       0.00       0.06       0.06 
#> -----------------------------------------------------------
#> 
#> Top variables:
#>              depth vimp.all vimp.setosa vimp.versicolor vimp.virginica
#> Petal.Length  1.03    0.618        1.45            2.12           1.42
#> Petal.Width   1.06    0.540        1.27            1.97           1.12
#> -----------------------------------------------------------

## ------------------------------------------------------------
## regression example
## ------------------------------------------------------------
if (FALSE) {
# ... or load a cached randomForestSRC object
data(varsel_airq, package="ggRandomForests")

# Get a data.frame containing minimaldepth measures
gg_dta<- gg_minimal_depth(varsel_airq)
print(gg_dta)

# To nicely print a rfsrc::var.select output...
print(varsel_airq)
}
